<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><usx version="2">
  <chapter number="12" style="c" />
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" />In that day you will say, “I will give thanks to you, Yahweh; for though you were angry with me, your anger has turned away and you comfort me. <verse number="2" style="v" />Behold, God is my salvation. I will trust, and will not be afraid; for Yah, Yahweh, is my strength and song; and he has become my salvation.” <verse number="3" style="v" />Therefore with joy you will draw water out of the wells of salvation. <verse number="4" style="v" />In that day you will say, “Give thanks to Yahweh! Call on his name. Declare his doings among the peoples. Proclaim that his name is exalted! <verse number="5" style="v" />Sing to Yahweh, for he has done excellent things! Let this be known in all the earth! <verse number="6" style="v" />Cry aloud and shout, you inhabitant of Zion; for the Holy One of Israel is great among you!”</para>
</usx>